                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/407: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-13T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. Your 462, October 8, 8 p.m. did not reach the Department in time to get a
                    reply to you before meeting of Legations in Peking. Please wire me result of the
                    meeting and attitude of different governments as to the collection of Canton
                    taxes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
